comments.body: The Fold method throws EmptyCollectionFoldException when source is empty, which is good. However, calling source.Any() and then source.ToList() causes enumeration twice, which can be inefficient for large or streaming collections. Consider using an enumerator directly to avoid multiple enumerations.

comments.body: The Map method is implemented as an extension method, but the Filter and Fold methods are not. For consistency, consider making all higher-order functions extension methods or none. Also, the Map method uses the same input and output type T, limiting flexibility. Consider adding Map with different input and output types (e.g., Map<TSource, TResult>).
